observations.recommendation:
1) To review and reevaluate the provisions cited in the Septage and Sewage Management Ordinance (SSMO) of the Municipality, and propose the enactment of the revised ordinance, after considering the corrections and amendments thereto, to conform with pertinent guidelines on septage and sewage management system;
2) To ensure full compliance with the policy and guidelines stipulated in DILG Memorandum Circular 2019-62 dated April 22, 2019, and its adherence with the provisions of the Philippine Clean Water Act of 2004; and
3) To prioritize projects that can address pollution prevention, control, and abatement in the water resources.

Municipal Accountant:
1) Prepare the Journal Voucher (JV) to record the beginning balance of the local road network and its components in the general ledger and the Local Road Network Ledger Card (format attached as Annex B), respectively;
2) Support the JV with the Registry of Public Infrastructures for Roads, working papers on the distribution of costs for the road components, and working papers on the determination of the depreciated replacement cost for road components with no available cost per registry;
3) Keep and maintain subsidiary records for roads and road components for every road network; and
Municipal General Services Officer:
1) Maintain a Local Road Inventory and Road Map;
2) Conduct a physical count and prepare the Report on the Physical Count of the Road Network System;
3) Keep a complete Local Road Network Property Card (Annex C) for all roads and their components; and
4) Prepare the Report of the Local Road Network (Annex D) of the MLGU of Libungan.
Municipal Engineer:
Provide the Municipal Accountant and the GSO with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects.

